main event: A naval message reported the sighting of an unidentified flying object resembling a first magnitude star on July 23, 1962.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for twenty-five minutes., The object was observed by the bridge crew of USS Falgout and confirmed by the commanding officer., The object disappeared into low clouds near the horizon., The sighting occurred on a bright moonlit night with seven tenths cloud coverage., The course of the object was east-northeast.
sighted object: object resembling a first magnitude star
